Entity.Name: Museum of Glass
Entity.Description: It began in August, 1992 in the course of a conversation between two friends, Phil Phibbs, who had recently retired as president of the University of Puget Sound and artist Dale Chihuly who had grown up in a neighborhood near the campus and had attended the university. Dr. Phibbs suggested that Tacoma should have a glass museum. He reasoned that artists from the Pacific Northwest had played a major role in the Studio Glass movement as it developed around the world.
Entity.Address: 1801 Dock Street, Tacoma, WA, 98421

Entity.Name: Cafe Brosseau
Entity.Description: A family friendly cafe where the coffee and food are local and fresh. It's named to honor the history of the building, the area, and because we like how the name sounds! To pronounce it just think "Brew-So." Appropriate for a coffee shop, n'est-ce pas?
Entity.Address: 2716 North 21st Street, Tacoma WA 98406 USA

Entity.Name: O'Blarney's Irish Pub
Entity.Description: Lively fare of  great food, drinks, games and good times. Friendly staff, welcoming atmosphere and good food make O’Blarney’s Irish Pub one of the area’s favorite pubs.
Entity.Address: 4411 Martin Way East, Olympia WA 98516 USA

Entity.Name: New Moon Cafe
Entity.Description: One of the best kept secrets in Olympia, Washington for breakfast and lunch. New Moon Cafe pride themselves in fresh ingredients, consistent quality, amazing prices, and an atmosphere that feels just like home. They never cut corners: all their salad dressings, hashbrowns, and their famous Blackberry Jam are all homemade!
Entity.Address: 113 4th Ave W, Olympia WA 98501 USA

Entity.Name: Great Wolf Lodge
Entity.Description: Your Great Wolf Lodge adventure begins in our massive, 84-degree indoor water park. Splash the day away in over 56,000 square feet of water-packed excitement, including jaw-dropping slides for thrill seekers or zero-depth entry areas for little ones. Outside the water park, the fun continues. Grab a wand and battle a dragon in MagiQuest or get an ice cream-themed manicure in Scooops Kid Spa before gathering your family in our Grand Lobby for nightly fireside Story Time, the perfect ending to a Great Wolf day.
Entity.Address: 20500 Old Highway 99 SW, Grand Mound 98531 WA USA

Entity.Name: Chehalis-Centralia Railroad and Museum
Entity.Description: The Chehalis-Centralia Railroad & Museum is a non-profit organization based in Washington State. It’s goal is to preserve the logging and railroading heritage of Lewis County in specific, and Southwest Washington State in general, in the form of a railroad and a historic, living museum.
Entity.Address: 1101 SW Sylvenus St., Chehalis WA 98532 USA

Entity.Name: Las Tarascas
Entity.Description: Authentic Mexican Food Family owned and operated since 1997.
Entity.Address: 1001 W Main St, Centralia WA 98531 USA

Entity.Name: Travel Inn Resort
Entity.Description: Strategically located at the gateway to Ocean and Mountain recreation, just 30 minutes away from the Coastal Beaches. Local rivers and streams have Salmon, Steelhead and Trout, while the surrounding forests abound in game birds, deer and elk. Nearby Westport offers some of the best seafood and fishing in the world. Activities at the park include swimming pool, pickle ball and pot lucks.
Entity.Address: 801 E Main Street, Elma WA 98541 USA
